author: Laura Kusisto
title: Clouds Descend on Spring Home Sales
text:
The economy is booming, take-home pay is rising and millennials are getting married and having children. Despite all those homebuying catalysts, this could be one of the weakest spring selling seasons in recent years.
The culprits: rising mortgage rates, a tax bill that reduces the incentives for homeownership and a growing weariness among first-buyers being priced out of the marketâ€”all of which are expected to damp demand for homes this year.
